LOUISVILLE, Ky. (WHAS11) - The University of Louisville women's golf team took home their fourth consecutive Cardinal Cup Tuesday at the UofL Golf Club. 
The Cards beat out four top-50 programs, including East Carolina, Notre Dame, Florida State and Illinois, on their way to winning the tournament with a 14 over par tally. 
In addition to the team title, the program took seven of the top 25 spots for individual performers. Freshman Lexie Long placed tops out of the Lady Cards squad, tying for 3rd individually.
